Entity Note

# Note is the unified logbook entity. It covers:
#   - Manual entries (end-of-day journal, quick capture, free-form notes)
#   - Automatic entries generated by Sistema in response to domain events
# The type field differentiates them. Manual notes are created by Usuario.
# Automatic notes are created by Sistema via the create_automatic_note event.

Schema
  note_id         UUID        primary key
  space_id        UUID        foreign key → Space
  type            NoteType    required
  title           string      optional    — manual notes may have a title
  body            string      required    — markdown text
  note_date       date        required    — defaults to today for manual notes
                                            user can change to a past date
                                            system sets to event date for automatic notes
  reference_id    UUID        optional    — id of the entity this note is about
  reference_type  EntityType  optional    — type of the referenced entity

Catalogs
  NoteType
    manual                   — free-form entry by Usuario
    task_created             — Sistema: a task was manually created
    task_generated           — Sistema: a task was generated from an Activity
    task_status_changed      — Sistema: a task transitioned between statuses
    task_autoclosed          — Sistema: Sistema autoclosed a task
    task_comment_added       — Sistema: a comment was added to a task
    activity_created         — Sistema: an activity was created
    note_edited              — Sistema: a manual note was edited
    calendar_entry_created   — Sistema: a calendar entry was created
    summary_generated        — Sistema: a summary was generated or updated

  EntityType
    Task
    Activity
    CalendarEntry
    Summary

States
  status    Active | Archived
